Text: Up, Up, and Away was one of the first songs I EVER heard on (my own) radio, living on the Navy base in Yokosuka Japan 1966 - 1968 and tuned in to whatever the armed forces radio station was in the late 60s.  "Next up - Otis Redding and On the Dock of the Bay."  heh.  Goddamn, those chicks on the  album cover are HOT.
